<dl id="n30174c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30174c">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30174c"> 174(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> into heart fright / skin = sweat / eyes = tears</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The overflow of the nerve-energy may be <mark>into the heart, accelerating it, into the sweat glands and the tear glands, making them active</mark>, and into the body muscles, throwing them into a greater or less degree of tremor. This is the physiology of &ldquo;to dream of the devil and wake in a fright&rdquo; (Ingoldsby Legends) <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 65</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
